                 <exercise>
                    <title>Problems</title>
                    <task workspace="8in">
                        <statement>
                            <p>
                            Give an example of a function <m>f</m> and an interval <m>[a,b]</m> for which we know <m>\int_{a}^{b}f</m> does not exist.
                            </p>
                        </statement>
                    </task>

                    <task workspace="8in">
                        <statement>
                            <p>
                            Is the function in Problem 9.9 integrable over <m>[0,1]</m>? If so, determine the value of the corresponding integral.
If not, explain why.
                            </p>
                        </statement>
